{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Everyone's familiar with cancer,"},{"time":4000,"text":"but we don't normally think of cancer"},{"time":6000,"text":"as being a contagious disease."},{"time":10000,"text":"The Tasmanian devil has shown us"},{"time":12000,"text":"that, not only can cancer be a contagious disease,"},{"time":15000,"text":"but it can also threaten"},{"time":17000,"text":"an entire species with extinction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"So first of all, what is a Tasmanian devil?"},{"time":25000,"text":"Many of you might be familiar with Taz, the cartoon character,"},{"time":28000,"text":"the one that spins around and around and around."},{"time":30000,"text":"But not many people know"},{"time":32000,"text":"that there actually is a real animal called the Tasmanian devil,"},{"time":35000,"text":"and it's the world's largest carnivorous marsupial."},{"time":39000,"text":"A marsupial is a mammal with a pouch"},{"time":41000,"text":"like a kangaroo."},{"time":43000,"text":"The Tasmanian devil got its name"},{"time":45000,"text":"from the terrifying nocturnal scream that it makes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49000,"text":"(Screaming)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":62000,"text":"The Tasmanian devil is predominantly a scavenger,"},{"time":65000,"text":"and it uses its powerful jaws"},{"time":67000,"text":"and its sharp teeth"},{"time":69000,"text":"to chomp on the bones of rotting dead animals."},{"time":72000,"text":"[The] Tasmanian devil is found only on the island of Tasmania,"},{"time":75000,"text":"which is that small island"},{"time":77000,"text":"just to the south of the mainland of Australia."},{"time":79000,"text":"And despite their ferocious appearance,"},{"time":83000,"text":"Tasmanian devils are actually"},{"time":85000,"text":"quite adorable little animals."},{"time":88000,"text":"In fact, growing up in Tasmania,"},{"time":90000,"text":"it always was incredibly exciting"},{"time":92000,"text":"when we got a chance to see"},{"time":94000,"text":"a Tasmanian devil in the wild."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"But the Tasmanian devil population"},{"time":98000,"text":"has been undergoing a really extremely fast decline."},{"time":102000,"text":"And in fact, there's concern"},{"time":104000,"text":"that the species could go extinct in the wild"},{"time":107000,"text":"within 20 to 30 years."},{"time":110000,"text":"And the reason for that"},{"time":112000,"text":"is the emergence of a new disease,"},{"time":114000,"text":"a contagious cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"The story begins in 1996"},{"time":120000,"text":"when a wildlife photographer took this photograph here"},{"time":123000,"text":"of a Tasmanian devil"},{"time":125000,"text":"with a large tumor on its face."},{"time":127000,"text":"At the time, this was thought to be a one-off."},{"time":130000,"text":"Animals, just like humans,"},{"time":132000,"text":"sometimes get strange tumors."},{"time":135000,"text":"However, we now believe"},{"time":137000,"text":"that this is the first sighting of a new disease,"},{"time":140000,"text":"which is now an epidemic spreading through Tasmania."},{"time":144000,"text":"The disease was first sighted"},{"time":146000,"text":"in the northeast of Tasmania in 1996"},{"time":149000,"text":"and has spread across Tasmania like a huge wave."},{"time":152000,"text":"Now there's only a small part of the population,"},{"time":155000,"text":"which remains unaffected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157000,"text":"This disease appears first as tumors,"},{"time":160000,"text":"usually on the face or inside the mouth"},{"time":162000,"text":"of affected Tasmanian devils."},{"time":164000,"text":"These tumors inevitably grow into larger tumors,"},{"time":167000,"text":"such as these ones here."},{"time":169000,"text":"And the next image I'm going to show"},{"time":171000,"text":"is quite gruesome."},{"time":173000,"text":"But inevitably, these tumors progress"},{"time":175000,"text":"towards being enormous, ulcerating tumors like this one here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"This one in particular sticks in my mind,"},{"time":183000,"text":"because this is the first case of this disease"},{"time":185000,"text":"that I saw myself."},{"time":187000,"text":"And I remember the horror of seeing this little female devil"},{"time":190000,"text":"with this huge ulcerating, foul-smelling tumor"},{"time":192000,"text":"inside her mouth"},{"time":194000,"text":"that had actually cracked off her entire lower jaw."},{"time":198000,"text":"She hadn't eaten for days."},{"time":201000,"text":"Her guts were swimming with parasitic worms."},{"time":203000,"text":"Her body was riddled with secondary tumors."},{"time":206000,"text":"And yet, she was feeding three little baby Tasmanian devils"},{"time":209000,"text":"in her pouch."},{"time":212000,"text":"Of course, they died along with the mother."},{"time":215000,"text":"They were too young to survive without their mother."},{"time":218000,"text":"In fact, in the area where she comes from,"},{"time":221000,"text":"more than 90 percent of the Tasmanian devil population"},{"time":224000,"text":"has already died of this disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"Scientists around the world"},{"time":229000,"text":"were intrigued by this cancer,"},{"time":231000,"text":"this infectious cancer,"},{"time":233000,"text":"that was spreading through the Tasmanian devil population."},{"time":236000,"text":"And our minds immediately turned to cervical cancer in women,"},{"time":239000,"text":"which is spread by a virus,"},{"time":241000,"text":"and to the AIDS epidemic,"},{"time":243000,"text":"which is associated with a number of different types of cancer."},{"time":247000,"text":"All the evidence suggested that this devil cancer"},{"time":250000,"text":"was spread by a virus."},{"time":253000,"text":"However, we now know -- and I'll tell you right now --"},{"time":256000,"text":"that we know that this cancer is not spread by a virus."},{"time":259000,"text":"In fact, the infectious agent of disease in this cancer"},{"time":263000,"text":"is something altogether more sinister,"},{"time":265000,"text":"and something that we hadn't really thought of before."},{"time":268000,"text":"But in order for me to explain what that is,"},{"time":271000,"text":"I need to spend just a couple of minutes"},{"time":273000,"text":"talking more about cancer itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276000,"text":"Cancer is a disease"},{"time":278000,"text":"that affects millions of people around the world every year."},{"time":281000,"text":"One in three people in this room"},{"time":283000,"text":"will develop cancer at some stage in their lives."},{"time":286000,"text":"I myself had a tumor removed from my large intestine"},{"time":288000,"text":"when I was only 14."},{"time":291000,"text":"Cancer occurs"},{"time":293000,"text":"when a single cell in your body"},{"time":295000,"text":"acquires a set of random mutations in important genes"},{"time":298000,"text":"that cause that cell to start to produce"},{"time":301000,"text":"more and more and more copies of itself."},{"time":305000,"text":"Paradoxically, once established,"},{"time":308000,"text":"natural selection actually favors"},{"time":310000,"text":"the continued growth of cancer."},{"time":312000,"text":"Natural selection is survival of the fittest."},{"time":315000,"text":"And when you have a population of fast-dividing cancer cells,"},{"time":318000,"text":"if one of them acquires new mutations,"},{"time":320000,"text":"which allow them to grow more quickly,"},{"time":322000,"text":"acquire nutrients more successfully,"},{"time":324000,"text":"invade the body,"},{"time":326000,"text":"they'll be selected for by evolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329000,"text":"That's why cancer is such a difficult disease to treat."},{"time":333000,"text":"It evolves."},{"time":335000,"text":"Throw a drug at it,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and resistant cells will grow back."},{"time":340000,"text":"An amazing fact is that,"},{"time":342000,"text":"given the right environment and the right nutrients,"},{"time":345000,"text":"a cancer cell has the potential"},{"time":347000,"text":"to go on growing forever."},{"time":350000,"text":"However cancer is constrained"},{"time":352000,"text":"by living inside our bodies,"},{"time":354000,"text":"and its continued growth,"},{"time":356000,"text":"its spreading through our bodies"},{"time":358000,"text":"and eating away at our tissues,"},{"time":360000,"text":"leads to the death of the cancer patient"},{"time":363000,"text":"and also to the death of the cancer itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367000,"text":"So cancer could be thought of"},{"time":369000,"text":"as a strange, short-lived, self-destructive life form --"},{"time":374000,"text":"an evolutionary dead end."},{"time":378000,"text":"But that is where the Tasmanian devil cancer"},{"time":380000,"text":"has acquired an absolutely amazing"},{"time":383000,"text":"evolutionary adaptation."},{"time":386000,"text":"And the answer came from studying"},{"time":388000,"text":"the Tasmanian devil cancer's DNA."},{"time":390000,"text":"This was work from many people,"},{"time":392000,"text":"but I'm going to explain it through a confirmatory experiment"},{"time":394000,"text":"that I did a few years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396000,"text":"The next slide is going to be gruesome."},{"time":399000,"text":"This is Jonas."},{"time":401000,"text":"He's a Tasmanian devil that we found"},{"time":404000,"text":"with a large tumor on his face."},{"time":406000,"text":"And being a geneticist,"},{"time":408000,"text":"I'm always interested to look at DNA and mutations."},{"time":411000,"text":"So I took this opportunity"},{"time":413000,"text":"to collect some samples from Jonas' tumor"},{"time":415000,"text":"and also some samples from other parts of his body."},{"time":418000,"text":"I took these back to the lab."},{"time":420000,"text":"I extracted DNA from them."},{"time":422000,"text":"And when I looked at the sequence of the DNA,"},{"time":425000,"text":"and compared the sequence of Jonas' tumor"},{"time":428000,"text":"to that of the rest of his body,"},{"time":430000,"text":"I discovered that they had a completely different genetic profile."},{"time":435000,"text":"In fact, Jonas and his tumor"},{"time":437000,"text":"were as different from each other"},{"time":440000,"text":"as you and the person sitting next to you."},{"time":443000,"text":"What this told us was that Jonas' tumor"},{"time":446000,"text":"did not arise from cells of his own body."},{"time":449000,"text":"In fact, more genetic profiling"},{"time":452000,"text":"told us that this tumor in Jonas"},{"time":454000,"text":"actually probably first arose"},{"time":456000,"text":"from the cells of a female Tasmanian devil --"},{"time":458000,"text":"and Jonas was clearly a male."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460000,"text":"So how come"},{"time":462000,"text":"a tumor that arose from the cells of another individual"},{"time":465000,"text":"is growing on Jonas' face?"},{"time":468000,"text":"Well the next breakthrough"},{"time":470000,"text":"came from studying hundreds of Tasmanian devil cancers"},{"time":473000,"text":"from all around Tasmania."},{"time":475000,"text":"We found that all of these cancers"},{"time":477000,"text":"shared the same DNA."},{"time":479000,"text":"Think about that for a minute."},{"time":481000,"text":"That means that all of these cancers"},{"time":483000,"text":"actually are the same cancer"},{"time":485000,"text":"that arose once from one individual devil,"},{"time":488000,"text":"that have broken free of that first devil's body"},{"time":491000,"text":"and spread through the entire Tasmanian devil population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495000,"text":"But how can a cancer spread in a population?"},{"time":498000,"text":"Well the final piece of the puzzle came"},{"time":500000,"text":"when we remember how devils behave when they meet each other in the wild."},{"time":503000,"text":"They tend to bite each other,"},{"time":505000,"text":"often quite ferociously and usually on the face."},{"time":508000,"text":"We think that cancer cells"},{"time":511000,"text":"actually come off the tumor, get into the saliva."},{"time":514000,"text":"When the devil bites another devil,"},{"time":516000,"text":"it actually physically implants living cancer cells into the next devil,"},{"time":519000,"text":"so the tumor continues to grow."},{"time":521000,"text":"So this Tasmanian devil cancer"},{"time":523000,"text":"is perhaps the ultimate cancer."},{"time":525000,"text":"It's not constrained by living within the body that gave rise to it."},{"time":528000,"text":"It spreads through the population,"},{"time":530000,"text":"has mutations that allow it to evade the immune system,"},{"time":533000,"text":"and it's the only cancer that we know of"},{"time":535000,"text":"that's threatening an entire species with extinction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539000,"text":"But if this can happen in Tasmanian devils,"},{"time":542000,"text":"why hasn't it happened in other animals"},{"time":544000,"text":"or even humans?"},{"time":546000,"text":"Well the answer is, it has."},{"time":550000,"text":"This is Kimbo."},{"time":552000,"text":"He's a dog that belongs to a family in Mombasa in Kenya."},{"time":556000,"text":"Last year, his owner noticed some blood"},{"time":559000,"text":"trickling from his genital region."},{"time":562000,"text":"She took him to the vet"},{"time":564000,"text":"and the vet discovered something quite disgusting."},{"time":567000,"text":"And if you're squeamish, please look away now."},{"time":570000,"text":"He discovered this,"},{"time":572000,"text":"a huge bleeding tumor"},{"time":574000,"text":"at the base of Kimbo's penis."},{"time":578000,"text":"The vet diagnosed this as transmissible venereal tumor,"},{"time":581000,"text":"a sexually transmitted cancer"},{"time":584000,"text":"that affects dogs."},{"time":586000,"text":"And just as the Tasmanian devil cancer is contagious"},{"time":589000,"text":"through the spread of living cancer cells,"},{"time":591000,"text":"so is this dog cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593000,"text":"But this dog cancer is quite remarkable,"},{"time":595000,"text":"because it spread all around the world."},{"time":597000,"text":"And in fact, these same cells"},{"time":599000,"text":"that are affecting Kimbo here"},{"time":602000,"text":"are also found affecting dogs"},{"time":604000,"text":"in New York City,"},{"time":606000,"text":"in mountain villages in the Himalayas"},{"time":608000,"text":"and in Outback Australia."},{"time":611000,"text":"We also believe this cancer might be very old."},{"time":613000,"text":"In fact, genetic profiling tells"},{"time":615000,"text":"that it may be tens of thousands of years old,"},{"time":618000,"text":"which means that this cancer"},{"time":620000,"text":"may have first arisen"},{"time":622000,"text":"from the cells of a wolf"},{"time":624000,"text":"that lived alongside the Neanderthals."},{"time":627000,"text":"This cancer is remarkable."},{"time":629000,"text":"It's the oldest mammalian-derived life form that we know of."},{"time":633000,"text":"It's a living relic"},{"time":635000,"text":"of the distant past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"So we've seen that this can happen in animals."},{"time":641000,"text":"Could cancers be contagious between people?"},{"time":646000,"text":"Well this is a question"},{"time":648000,"text":"which fascinated Chester Southam,"},{"time":650000,"text":"a cancer doctor in the 1950s."},{"time":653000,"text":"Ad he decided to put this to the test"},{"time":656000,"text":"by actually deliberately inoculating people"},{"time":659000,"text":"with cancer from somebody else."},{"time":662000,"text":"And this is a photograph of Dr. Southam in 1957"},{"time":666000,"text":"injecting cancer into a volunteer,"},{"time":669000,"text":"who in this case was an inmate"},{"time":671000,"text":"in Ohio State Penitentiary."},{"time":675000,"text":"Most of the people that Dr. Southam injected"},{"time":677000,"text":"did not go on to develop cancer"},{"time":679000,"text":"from the injected cells."},{"time":681000,"text":"But a small number of them did,"},{"time":683000,"text":"and they were mostly people who were otherwise ill --"},{"time":686000,"text":"whose immune systems were probably compromised."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691000,"text":"What this tells us,"},{"time":693000,"text":"ethical issues aside,"},{"time":695000,"text":"is that ..."},{"time":697000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":699000,"text":"it's probably extremely rare"},{"time":702000,"text":"for cancers to be transferred between people."},{"time":706000,"text":"However, under some circumstances,"},{"time":708000,"text":"it can happen."},{"time":711000,"text":"And I think that this is something"},{"time":713000,"text":"that oncologists and epidemiologists"},{"time":715000,"text":"should be aware of in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718000,"text":"So just finally,"},{"time":720000,"text":"cancer is an inevitable outcome"},{"time":722000,"text":"of the ability of our cells"},{"time":724000,"text":"to divide"},{"time":726000,"text":"and to adapt to their environments."},{"time":729000,"text":"But that does not mean that we should give up hope"},{"time":732000,"text":"in the fight against cancer."},{"time":734000,"text":"In fact, I believe, given more knowledge"},{"time":736000,"text":"of the complex evolutionary processes that drive cancer's growth,"},{"time":739000,"text":"we can defeat cancer."},{"time":742000,"text":"My personal aim"},{"time":744000,"text":"is to defeat the Tasmanian devil cancer."},{"time":748000,"text":"Let's prevent the Tasmanian devil"},{"time":750000,"text":"from being the first animal"},{"time":752000,"text":"to go extinct from cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}